WEBVTT

00:02.394 --> 00:03.727
<i> -Previously on</i> Monarch...
-And y'all saw her last night.

00:03.746 --> 00:05.820
<i> That was not a woman</i>
<i> who was just about to die.</i>

00:05.840 --> 00:07.339
<i> Something doesn't make sense.</i>

00:07.491 --> 00:08.749
<i> HARLEY:</i>
<i> She also left behind</i>

00:08.825 --> 00:09.842
<i> letters for her children.</i>

00:09.993 --> 00:12.994
<i> LUKE:</i>
<i> Nicky wrote these letters?</i>

00:13.014 --> 00:14.346
What the hell's
my sister hiding?

00:14.573 --> 00:17.574
♪<i> How do I live without you?</i> ♪

00:17.667 --> 00:19.593
<i> NICKY:</i>
<i> So you stayed out</i>
<i> of the spotlight because</i>

00:19.745 --> 00:21.078
you thought you'd outshine me?

00:21.171 --> 00:23.080
Well, there can
only be one queen.

00:23.173 --> 00:24.915
My name is Catt Phoenix,

00:24.933 --> 00:27.601
and my daughter Ana and I have
an appointment with Luke Roman.

00:27.695 --> 00:30.178
I am so sorry. We must
have double-booked y'all.

00:30.197 --> 00:31.755
There are millions of people

00:31.774 --> 00:33.273
trying
to be country singers, Mom.

00:33.425 --> 00:34.608
Yes, but they're not you.

00:34.760 --> 00:35.868
We can't play "Love of my Life."

00:36.019 --> 00:37.352
There's an issue
with the rights.

00:37.446 --> 00:38.945
Hell I can't. We own
the whole damn catalogue.

00:39.098 --> 00:41.114
Please. We could get sued.

00:41.267 --> 00:43.375
Nick, it's over, all right?
I ended it.

00:43.602 --> 00:45.544
How old is she
this time Clive, hmm?

00:45.695 --> 00:47.938
She able to vote?

00:48.031 --> 00:50.532
Not me I'm worried about.
It's Luke.

00:50.626 --> 00:51.775
He's always alone.

00:51.868 --> 00:53.794
This is wrong.

00:53.888 --> 00:55.629
<i> We have to stop this.</i>

00:55.723 --> 00:57.281
<i> I love Gigi.</i>

00:57.415 --> 00:59.616
A Roman never forgets a friend.

00:59.635 --> 01:01.510
Or an enemy.

01:01.620 --> 01:03.520
(gunshot)

01:07.810 --> 01:10.152
Yeah, I need you
to run some tags for me.

01:14.967 --> 01:17.076
(knocking)

01:17.227 --> 01:18.802
Good evening, Ms. Roman.

01:18.821 --> 01:20.579
-Evening.
-I hate to bother you this late.

01:20.730 --> 01:22.823
You mind if I have a few words
with your father?

01:22.975 --> 01:24.583
NICKY:
Oh, he's in bed.

01:24.734 --> 01:26.476
-Really?
-NICKY: Mm-hmm.

01:26.570 --> 01:28.812
I just saw his truck
down near the woods

01:28.905 --> 01:32.073
by Enchanted Rock
about an hour ago.

01:32.093 --> 01:33.741
It's kind of late
for him to be out there.

01:33.836 --> 01:35.836
Yeah, he went for a drive.

01:35.930 --> 01:39.172
Um, he got back
and turned in a while ago.

01:39.325 --> 01:41.517
Do you want me
to go wake him up?

01:43.753 --> 01:46.346
No need. Just wanted
to make sure he got home okay.

01:46.498 --> 01:49.166
All right.
That's sweet. Thank you.

01:49.184 --> 01:52.194
-Have a good evening.
-Good night.

02:04.032 --> 02:06.016
(sighs)

02:06.034 --> 02:08.210
So? What do you think?

02:10.038 --> 02:12.614
I think she's lying
through her teeth.

02:12.633 --> 02:14.383
(car starts up outside)

02:17.787 --> 02:19.045
All right, they're gone.

02:19.140 --> 02:21.715
-Not for long.
-What?

02:21.809 --> 02:23.200
In about 40 minutes,

02:23.293 --> 02:24.977
they're either gonna show up
here with a warrant,

02:25.128 --> 02:26.628
or they're gonna go back
out there and start digging.

02:26.722 --> 02:28.221
Right. So what are you saying?

02:28.374 --> 02:31.191
I'm saying we better get
to that body before they do.

02:36.806 --> 02:40.242
