♪<i> Blame it on my juice</i> ♪

04:09.491 --> 04:12.567
♪<i> Blame it,</i>
<i> blame it on my juice, uh-uh.</i> ♪

04:12.586 --> 04:13.994
I cannot wait to see you

04:14.146 --> 04:15.645
light up the Queens of Country
with that!

04:15.664 --> 04:18.648
I cannot wait to see her
wipe the floor with Nicky.

04:18.667 --> 04:22.002
Oh! Sister rivalry
is the best rivalry.

04:22.154 --> 04:25.005
Ugh. I hate that everything has
to be a competition.

04:25.157 --> 04:27.582
-I love Nicky.
-Well, so do I.

04:27.601 --> 04:29.268
But what can I say?
People like a little

04:29.495 --> 04:31.328
<i> Game of Thrones</i>
with their country music.

04:31.346 --> 04:33.513
When your mama
won her first crown,

04:33.665 --> 04:38.001
she sang circles
around both Reba and Dolly.

04:38.020 --> 04:39.594
I appreciate the support.

04:39.613 --> 04:41.596
I'm gonna go out there
and do my best,

04:41.615 --> 04:44.533
but this is not a competition,
and there is no rivalry.

04:46.269 --> 04:48.620
Her naivete is adorable.

04:48.772 --> 04:49.746
(laughs)

04:56.371 --> 04:58.797
Sorry, Mom. I'm taking mine
to go. Looks delicious, though.

04:59.024 --> 05:02.192
Well, don't forget your meds
and your... and your cleats.

05:02.194 --> 05:03.527
Yeah, I got it. See ya.

05:03.695 --> 05:04.970
And whatever else
you're gonna call me about

05:05.121 --> 05:07.288
-in the next two hours.
-He's 18 now.

05:07.382 --> 05:08.807
You could let him
forget about it.

05:08.958 --> 05:10.142
Maybe then he'd learn.

05:10.293 --> 05:12.719
Well, in that case,
shall I let you...

05:12.813 --> 05:15.555
you forget this?

05:15.707 --> 05:18.132
And here. Sweater.

05:18.152 --> 05:19.559
You've had a cold.
Put it on.

05:19.711 --> 05:21.061
Too bad
the Grammys don't have an award

05:21.213 --> 05:23.380
for helicopter parenting.
You'd finally get one.

05:23.398 --> 05:25.657
-Mm-hmm.
-Mm.
-CLIVE: Hey.

05:28.645 --> 05:31.312
What about me?
What should I remember?

05:31.332 --> 05:33.314
I'd say
to keep it in your pants,

05:33.334 --> 05:34.666
but I don't think
that's possible.

05:34.818 --> 05:36.001
I meant what I said, Nick.

05:36.228 --> 05:37.819
It's all behind me.

05:37.913 --> 05:39.987
I'm just about
to go to therapy now

05:40.040 --> 05:41.489
so I can deal
with why I'm so compelled

05:41.583 --> 05:43.900
to screw up the best thing
that ever happened to me.

05:43.993 --> 05:46.178
(door open, door closes)

05:46.329 --> 05:47.679
Nicky.

05:47.906 --> 05:49.831
(Clive sighs)

05:49.850 --> 05:51.908
-Hello, Clive.
-Luke.

05:51.927 --> 05:53.352
CLIVE:
Don't bother to knock.

05:53.579 --> 05:55.670
Uh, what brings you here
so early?

05:55.764 --> 05:58.648
We need to talk. Now.

06:00.027 --> 06:02.694
You're a bad liar, Nick.

06:02.771 --> 06:04.512
Even worse forger.

06:04.573 --> 06:07.866
This letter?
The one that Mama didn't write?

06:09.428 --> 06:12.037
-What, you gonna deny it?
-Well, I had to do something.

06:12.188 --> 06:14.021
You and Daddy were arguing,

06:14.041 --> 06:15.615
me and Gigi were
at each other's throats.

06:15.767 --> 06:17.934
-I just thought...
-What?

06:18.027 --> 06:19.360
That making up some fairy tale

06:19.380 --> 06:20.787
in Mama's handwriting
was gonna make it all better?

06:20.881 --> 06:22.697
We've all broken a commandment
somewhere along the line.

06:22.866 --> 06:24.124
I'm sure if you dig deep,

06:24.200 --> 06:26.443
you'll be able
to think of something.

06:26.461 --> 06:29.221
Besides, with the Queens
of Country concert coming up,

06:29.372 --> 06:31.539
I just... (sighs)
I don't know.

06:31.558 --> 06:33.483
I just want some peace
in this family.

06:33.485 --> 06:36.395
Well, speaking of,
I'm working something for you.

06:37.547 --> 06:39.973
Open Horizon's gonna come
to your rehearsal today.

06:40.067 --> 06:41.625
They're ready
to offer me my tour?

06:41.627 --> 06:45.795
Hmm. Think of it more
as a... negotiation.

06:45.889 --> 06:47.221
Fine.

06:47.241 --> 06:50.075
Oh, and I also know
that you've been

06:50.226 --> 06:51.317
poking around Mama's death,

06:51.470 --> 06:53.245
like one of us had something
to do with it.

06:53.321 --> 06:55.730
Now you have got
to stop harping on

06:55.749 --> 06:57.457
about these conspiracy theories.

06:58.401 --> 07:00.568
Yeah, I guess you're right.

07:00.587 --> 07:03.237
Just... sometimes

07:03.257 --> 07:06.383
let my imagination
get the better of me, I guess.

07:07.335 --> 07:09.819
<i> -(line ringing)</i>
-(door closes)

07:09.913 --> 07:11.913
<i> -MARYBETH: Coroner's office.</i>
-Hey.

07:11.932 --> 07:13.823
I'm tired of waiting.
Tell me what you got.

07:13.842 --> 07:16.509
Look, I need to go through
the official channels on this.

07:16.662 --> 07:18.419
<i> We're talking</i>
<i> about the potential, illegal,</i>

07:18.439 --> 07:20.755
<i> assisted suicide</i>
<i> of Dottie Roman.</i>

07:20.774 --> 07:22.256
Just tell me what you found.

07:22.276 --> 07:25.185
The prelim tox screen showed us
some questionable results.

07:25.337 --> 07:27.612
<i> We are running it again</i>
<i> as we speak.</i>

07:27.689 --> 07:30.173
But brace yourself, Luke,
because if my gut is correct...

07:30.266 --> 07:33.076
Then a member of my family's
going to jail.

07:36.348 --> 07:39.291
♪ ♪

07:42.913 --> 07:46.356
♪<i> Cause I can feel you breathe,</i>
<i> it's washing over me</i> ♪

07:46.374 --> 07:49.801
♪<i> And suddenly,</i>
<i> I'm melting into you</i> ♪

07:49.953 --> 07:51.861
♪<i> There's nothing left</i>
<i> to prove</i> ♪

07:51.880 --> 07:54.881
♪<i> And baby, all we need</i>
<i> is just to be</i> ♪

07:55.033 --> 07:56.641
Yeah. Great.

07:56.793 --> 07:58.310
♪<i> Caught up in the touch ♪</i>

07:58.461 --> 08:00.870
-♪<i> A slow and steady rush</i> ♪
-Hey.

08:00.889 --> 08:03.223
-Hi.
-♪<i> Baby, isn't that the way</i> ♪

08:03.375 --> 08:09.112
♪<i> That love's supposed to be?</i> ♪

08:11.325 --> 08:17.245
♪<i> I can feel you breathe.</i> ♪

08:21.651 --> 08:24.318
Nicky, meet Mackenzie Gates
from Open Horizon.

08:24.412 --> 08:25.837
-Hi.
-Hi.

08:25.989 --> 08:27.488
So you're the new Alec Graham.

08:27.508 --> 08:31.993
Not really. I pride myself on
my relationships with talent.

08:32.120 --> 08:34.904
Discovering new artists,
nurturing older ones.

08:34.998 --> 08:36.906
And which one am I?

08:36.925 --> 08:40.260
That's just it. I don't know.

08:40.412 --> 08:43.170
You have<i> something,</i> no doubt.

08:43.190 --> 08:45.415
But you took a back seat
to your mother for years.

08:45.433 --> 08:48.175
The spotlight
doesn't find everyone.

08:48.195 --> 08:49.844
Uh, no, it does not,
you're right,

08:49.863 --> 08:52.105
but I'm not everyone.

08:52.199 --> 08:53.698
I just need a chance.

08:53.925 --> 08:55.516
Chances aren't given.
They're seized.

08:55.610 --> 08:59.020
And if you're begging me
for a tour, you've already lost.

08:59.114 --> 09:02.932
Show me who you are
at the concert this weekend.

09:03.026 --> 09:05.126
Make<i> me</i> beg you.

09:06.955 --> 09:08.529
Always a pleasure, Mackenzie.

09:08.549 --> 09:10.257
Anything for the Romans.

09:12.719 --> 09:14.886
Well, I don't think
she replaced Alec Graham.

09:15.038 --> 09:16.279
-I think she ate him.
-(laughs)

09:16.448 --> 09:19.783
I told you, Nick.
It's just gamesmanship.

09:19.785 --> 09:21.634
She's a professional hard-ass.

09:21.711 --> 09:23.636
No, it's not just that.
She saw right through me.

09:23.730 --> 09:25.638
-What are you talking about?
-The whole thing.

09:25.791 --> 09:27.640
The song, the photos,
the whole performance.

09:27.734 --> 09:30.643
It's like, my marriage is
hanging by a thread, and...

09:30.796 --> 09:32.812
it's not real.

09:32.964 --> 09:34.814
It's not supposed
to be real, Nick.

09:34.908 --> 09:37.300
And anyway, you sounded great.

09:37.319 --> 09:39.302
I know it's been a long road,

09:39.395 --> 09:42.305
but just keep doing
what you're doing, okay?

09:42.307 --> 09:44.499
Your time will come.

09:46.161 --> 09:49.236
♪<i> When you go to sleep tonight</i> ♪

09:49.331 --> 09:52.924
♪<i> And the stars</i>
<i> are shining bright</i> ♪

09:53.151 --> 09:57.721
♪<i> And your day has been</i>
<i> weary and long</i> ♪

09:59.157 --> 10:03.101
♪<i> Just know now far away</i> ♪

10:03.328 --> 10:08.164
♪<i> Someone'll say</i>
<i> that they miss you</i> ♪

10:08.183 --> 10:10.525
♪<i> While you're away...</i> ♪

10:18.935 --> 10:20.526
(gasps)

10:20.679 --> 10:22.495
Oh, Clive.

10:29.463 --> 10:32.130
You son of a bitch.

10:35.636 --> 10:37.427
(door slams)

10:52.727 --> 10:55.136
(toilet flushing)

10:55.155 --> 10:58.031
(sighs) Tell that
to your therapist, Clive.

11:03.330 --> 11:04.904
-GIGI: You flushed 'em?
-NICKY: Luckily, it was

11:04.998 --> 11:06.406
a low-flow toilet,
so I fished 'em out,

11:06.500 --> 11:09.592
and I donated them
to the Austin women's shelter.

11:09.594 --> 11:11.652
Good. Happy ending.

11:11.746 --> 11:13.654
-Disgusting but happy.
-(laughs)

11:13.674 --> 11:16.065
-That's good.
-Yep.

11:16.084 --> 11:18.751
Oh, Geeg,
I still can't believe it.

11:18.904 --> 11:21.638
I mean, I know he's done it
before, but six months.

11:22.665 --> 11:24.574
Look. This is her.

11:24.592 --> 11:26.092
Imogen Lowe.

11:26.186 --> 11:27.501
She's an actress.

11:27.521 --> 11:31.005
He did that Hallmark movie
with her in Vancouver.

11:31.099 --> 11:35.342
Mm. Fake teeth, fake hair.
Fake hoo-hahs, too, probably.

11:35.362 --> 11:36.361
Yeah.

11:36.512 --> 11:38.196
So does this mean
you're finally gonna

11:38.347 --> 11:40.440
kick his skinny British ass
to the curb?

11:40.534 --> 11:41.774
I can't.

11:41.927 --> 11:44.110
According to Open Horizon,

11:44.262 --> 11:45.370
divorce doesn't go
with my brand.

11:45.597 --> 11:48.022
-Nicky.
-Well, Mama and Daddy had

11:48.099 --> 11:50.024
the perfect marriage,
and she proved

11:50.118 --> 11:52.377
that a woman
can have it all, so...

11:52.604 --> 11:55.939
now I'm expected
to keep up appearances.

11:55.957 --> 11:57.957
For who? Is this what you want

11:58.109 --> 11:59.718
your children thinking
that a marriage is?

11:59.945 --> 12:02.203
Lying and cheating?

12:02.222 --> 12:04.964
So you picked the wrong guy.
It's not your fault.

12:05.116 --> 12:08.542
And not everybody can be
as lucky as Mama was.

12:08.636 --> 12:13.306
She and Daddy genuinely loved
and respected each other.

12:13.382 --> 12:16.050
Every marriage has got
to start from there.

12:16.069 --> 12:18.403
I know mine does.

12:19.406 --> 12:21.147
Yeah.

12:21.299 --> 12:23.491
Yeah, I guess so.

12:27.322 --> 12:29.748
I feel terrible
doing this to Gigi.

12:29.899 --> 12:32.308
I can't keep coming here.

12:32.327 --> 12:34.811
-That's what you said last time.
-(sighs)

12:34.829 --> 12:36.904
-And the time before that.
-Right.

12:36.998 --> 12:38.906
(chuckles softly)

12:39.000 --> 12:42.168
(phone buzzing)

12:42.262 --> 12:46.489
(sighs) Hmm. Who is it?

12:46.491 --> 12:50.009
It's Nicky. She wants
to have lunch with me tomorrow.

12:50.161 --> 12:52.353
Do you have any idea
what this is about?

12:54.423 --> 12:58.184
Mama always told Nicky,
"Keep your friends close."

12:58.336 --> 13:00.445
Well, Nicky and I have never
really been friends.

13:00.672 --> 13:02.672
Then she's gonna keep you
even closer.

13:02.690 --> 13:05.024
♪ ♪

13:05.101 --> 13:07.026
♪<i> Better days are on the way</i> ♪

13:07.178 --> 13:10.079
♪<i> Yes, they're on the way...</i> ♪

13:10.940 --> 13:12.181
I'm starving, Grandpa.

13:12.242 --> 13:13.941
Well, we can't have that.

13:13.960 --> 13:16.461
They're here.

13:17.947 --> 13:18.963
You ready?

13:19.115 --> 13:20.373
We didn't come all the way

13:20.525 --> 13:22.542
from Albuquerque for nothing.

13:22.618 --> 13:24.360
You've worked really hard
on this.

13:24.453 --> 13:25.953
So, come on. You can do it.

13:25.972 --> 13:27.764
-Okay. Okay.
-Go, go on.

13:41.896 --> 13:44.155
(playing soft, gentle melody)

13:50.071 --> 13:52.288
(singing in Spanish)

14:06.905 --> 14:09.055
♪ ♪

14:18.191 --> 14:20.917
♪<i> 'Cause you are the rose</i> ♪

14:20.935 --> 14:23.361
(singing in Spanish)

14:23.512 --> 14:29.617
♪<i> I go through the brambles.</i> ♪

14:32.097 --> 14:33.946
(woman whoops)

14:34.099 --> 14:37.450
(applause, whistling)

14:37.602 --> 14:40.086
(crowd chatter)

14:43.608 --> 14:45.958
This is Ana, my daughter,
so you won't forget.

14:46.127 --> 14:47.944
Our number is right there
on the back.

14:48.037 --> 14:50.037
Call us anytime, day or night.

14:50.056 --> 14:52.307
Anytime you're ready
to sign her.

14:57.898 --> 15:00.023
(laughing):
That was amazing.

15:15.898 --> 15:17.957
NICKY:
Did you lose something?

15:19.994 --> 15:21.494
No.

15:21.570 --> 15:23.755
I mean, yeah, just must be
in another jacket or something.

15:23.906 --> 15:26.816
Yeah, it could be, or you might
want to check Lake Buchanan,

15:26.834 --> 15:29.243
'cause I'm pretty sure
that's where the sewage ends up.

15:29.262 --> 15:32.488
You know...
after you've flushed.

15:32.490 --> 15:34.748
-Oh, you wouldn't have.
-I wouldn't?

15:34.842 --> 15:37.435
Because... I think...

15:37.662 --> 15:39.720
maybe I... did?

15:39.831 --> 15:41.422
And, Clive,

15:41.441 --> 15:45.443
I found, uh, this charging
in the kitchen.

15:46.613 --> 15:48.947
You invited Imogen
to my house this weekend

15:49.098 --> 15:50.840
on the Roman family jet?

15:50.933 --> 15:52.525
For God's sake, Clive!

15:52.677 --> 15:53.952
-It's not what you think.
-You've been sleeping with her

15:54.179 --> 15:55.861
for six months, and that's
the best you can come up with?

15:55.956 --> 15:57.622
It's a good thing that you are

15:57.773 --> 15:59.940
an actor and not a writer.
That's all I can say.

16:00.034 --> 16:01.701
She's just coming here
so I can end it,

16:01.795 --> 16:04.128
-in person, face-to-face.
-Oh. Okay.

16:04.321 --> 16:06.372
-I mean, I owe her that!
-Such sensitivity.

16:07.300 --> 16:09.450
I'm really glad
that I found you that therapist,

16:09.469 --> 16:11.285
'cause she's clearing doing
an amazing job.

16:11.304 --> 16:14.363
Now the bed in the pool house
is already made up.

16:14.457 --> 16:16.140
I was gonna say,
be careful about the rats,

16:16.292 --> 16:20.061
but there's no need because...
you're gonna fit right in.

16:21.964 --> 16:24.148
♪ ♪

16:29.397 --> 16:32.991
Yeah, I'm gonna stay
with Dad again tonight.

16:33.142 --> 16:35.326
<i>He's still having a tough time,</i>
<i> but...</i>

16:35.478 --> 16:37.328
oh, I hate to miss
Summer's bedtime.

16:37.480 --> 16:39.146
Can you put the phone up
to her ear

16:39.315 --> 16:40.981
so I can sing her a lullaby?

16:41.001 --> 16:42.816
<i>She's already fast asleep, baby.</i>

16:42.836 --> 16:45.837
But you can sing it to me.

16:46.989 --> 16:51.325
♪<i> There's so much good</i>
<i> I want to do</i> ♪

16:51.344 --> 16:56.347
♪<i> But God knows</i>
<i> the bad that I've done</i> ♪

16:57.666 --> 17:02.520
♪<i> It only takes</i>
<i> one look at you</i> ♪

17:02.671 --> 17:07.233
♪<i> To see the one</i>
<i> I want to be become...</i> ♪

17:09.087 --> 17:11.195
♪ ♪

17:27.196 --> 17:29.696
KAYLA: Geeg told me about
Queens of Country. That's huge.

17:29.716 --> 17:31.090
Sure is.

17:33.444 --> 17:35.536
You haven't touched your lunch.

17:35.555 --> 17:38.372
Yeah, I don't know.
I'm not very hungry.

17:38.391 --> 17:40.058
I don't know.
Maybe it's the heat.

17:40.209 --> 17:42.602
Or your conscience.

17:43.730 --> 17:45.396
I know about you and my brother.

17:47.125 --> 17:49.959
How could you do that to Gigi?

17:49.977 --> 17:52.695
Do you know what that will do
to her if she finds out?

17:54.741 --> 17:56.991
It's wrong.

17:58.060 --> 17:59.560
I love Gigi.

17:59.579 --> 18:02.988
I will not let you
hurt my sister. Do you hear me?

18:03.157 --> 18:04.731
You need to end it.

18:04.826 --> 18:06.751
(clears throat)

18:10.832 --> 18:14.408
Right. To Gigi Tucker-Roman,

18:14.427 --> 18:18.304
who we're lucky enough
to have in our lives.

18:33.504 --> 18:36.856
You're not eating sushi,
and you're not drinking sake.

18:36.932 --> 18:39.158
How far along are you?

18:40.678 --> 18:42.361
Not very.

18:42.455 --> 18:44.196
Luke doesn't even know yet.

18:44.349 --> 18:48.459
Well, I can't imagine the...
burden that you're carrying.

18:48.611 --> 18:51.612
But if this was to get out,
it would hurt a lot of people

18:51.631 --> 18:53.113
that mean the world to me.

18:53.133 --> 18:55.007
Are you threatening me?

18:55.951 --> 18:58.210
The opposite. I'm...

18:58.363 --> 19:01.055
I'm asking you
to let me handle it.

19:06.704 --> 19:09.355
♪ ♪

19:15.229 --> 19:17.062
-Hey. What you got there?
-(dog barking)

19:17.215 --> 19:19.231
Uh, just some old photos.

19:19.400 --> 19:21.642
Queens of Country want to do
a memorial reel on Mama, so...

19:21.736 --> 19:25.079
Well, nobody's using pictures
of your mama without my say-so.

19:25.907 --> 19:27.981
Okay.

19:28.001 --> 19:29.909
Understood. I'll, um...

19:30.003 --> 19:31.410
I'll clear 'em with you first.

19:31.562 --> 19:33.153
Oh, and by the way,
you know what?

19:33.247 --> 19:37.508
It'd be nice if maybe you MC'd
or-or sang a song.

19:37.660 --> 19:39.084
Nice for who?

19:39.237 --> 19:41.179
After that mess
at Mama's funeral,

19:41.330 --> 19:44.740
we need to remind the world
who you are.

19:44.833 --> 19:46.684
You're the King of Country, Dad.

19:46.835 --> 19:49.336
You're the Texas Truth-Teller.

19:49.430 --> 19:51.505
(sighs)

19:51.599 --> 19:53.191
Okay.

19:54.602 --> 19:55.735
Seriously?

19:56.771 --> 19:57.844
Yeah.

19:57.864 --> 19:59.104
(chuckles):
Damn.

19:59.273 --> 20:01.590
Well, I didn't think
you'd do it.

20:01.684 --> 20:04.593
Well, there's something
you need to do for me.

20:04.612 --> 20:06.111
Find out who's got the rights
to our music

20:06.206 --> 20:07.705
and how the hell
you're gonna get it back.

20:07.932 --> 20:09.707
I'm into it, okay?

20:09.934 --> 20:11.500
Don't worry.

20:16.049 --> 20:18.441
Don't manage me.

20:18.534 --> 20:21.368
This is about more
than contracts and cash.

20:21.387 --> 20:24.055
Those albums are a piece
of me and your mama.

20:24.282 --> 20:26.131
I've lost enough
of her as it is.

20:26.226 --> 20:28.476
I'm not giving up any more.

20:30.730 --> 20:32.980
♪ ♪

20:41.466 --> 20:44.242
♪<i> I work a double shift</i>
<i> on Monday...</i> ♪

20:44.427 --> 20:46.744
I can't believe Mama saved
all of her old wardrobe.

20:46.895 --> 20:48.804
You find anything good,
Miss Tanya?

20:48.897 --> 20:53.042
Sorry, girls. Might as well
give it up right now.

20:54.495 --> 20:56.629
Not so fast, Tucker.

20:59.150 --> 21:02.151
Damn. Looks like your mama
just rose from the dead.

21:02.153 --> 21:03.836
NICKY:
Right?

21:03.930 --> 21:05.838
Geeg?

21:05.990 --> 21:07.431
Where'd you get those?

21:08.434 --> 21:11.343
NICKY:
Well, Mama left 'em to Daddy,

21:11.496 --> 21:12.937
and Daddy's not
gonna wear 'em, so...

21:13.088 --> 21:14.689
Take 'em off.

21:16.258 --> 21:19.001
-Give 'em to me.
-What?

21:19.020 --> 21:20.278
Take 'em off!

21:21.114 --> 21:23.531
Uh, all right.

21:32.683 --> 21:35.351
Um, I'm so sorry.

21:35.369 --> 21:38.671
Geeg? Geeg? No, Gee... Oh!

21:40.967 --> 21:42.783
(sighs):
Okay.

21:42.802 --> 21:44.693
What has gotten into you?

21:44.787 --> 21:47.713
Geeg, hold up.

21:47.865 --> 21:49.715
Mama promised me these boots.

21:49.867 --> 21:51.550
She knew what they meant to me.

21:51.702 --> 21:54.386
Course, she never really paid me
much mind in life.

21:54.539 --> 21:57.056
Not sure why I thought
she'd start after she died.

21:57.208 --> 21:59.132
She did her best.
I don't understand

21:59.226 --> 22:00.467
why you're always
tearing her down.

22:00.561 --> 22:03.303
And why are you always
building her up?

22:03.397 --> 22:05.548
She made you kill her, Nicky.

22:05.566 --> 22:09.142
What kind of a mother does that
to one of her kids?

22:09.162 --> 22:11.645
Now, I know
that you're the smart one

22:11.664 --> 22:13.405
and I barely
graduated high school,

22:13.499 --> 22:15.407
but seeing your parents
for who they really are

22:15.560 --> 22:17.576
does not make you bad, Nicky.

22:17.670 --> 22:19.670
It makes you whole.

22:22.900 --> 22:24.633
(vehicle door opens)

22:25.828 --> 22:27.327
(door closes)

22:27.347 --> 22:29.555
♪ ♪

22:31.834 --> 22:33.909
♪<i> When someone's coming at you</i> ♪

22:33.928 --> 22:36.479
♪<i> And coming on strong...</i> ♪

22:37.582 --> 22:39.415
Mr. Roman?

22:39.508 --> 22:40.749
Afternoon.

22:40.768 --> 22:41.934
I wanted to ask you

22:42.086 --> 22:43.694
why I haven't heard back
from you

22:43.771 --> 22:45.345
about signing my daughter Ana.

22:45.365 --> 22:48.090
-Her heart is set
on Monarch, and she's...
-Listen.

22:48.259 --> 22:51.427
No BS, all right?
Your daughter's got chops.

22:51.445 --> 22:54.113
-Yes.
-But the business is handled
by the suits.

22:54.207 --> 22:56.207
And I don't look
like one of them, do I?

22:56.358 --> 22:58.300
-(chuckling): No. No.
-Okay.

22:58.360 --> 23:00.694
We were supposed
to meet with your son Luke,

23:00.788 --> 23:03.047
but we haven't heard back
from him, either.

23:03.198 --> 23:05.132
That's no surprise.

23:06.368 --> 23:09.111
I'm sorry. I-I got enough issues
with my son.

23:09.130 --> 23:11.138
I'll let this one be yours.

23:13.968 --> 23:15.643
Thank you.

23:37.141 --> 23:40.251
Look, Mama. I'm the queen,
just like you.

23:41.312 --> 23:44.755
You are nothing like me.
Nothing!

23:44.907 --> 23:48.909
Don't you ever
touch these boots again.

23:48.928 --> 23:50.177
You hear me?

23:54.934 --> 23:59.061
<i> You are nothing like me.</i>
<i> Nothing!</i>

24:16.271 --> 24:18.664
Mama, what were you hiding?

24:32.621 --> 24:34.029
(sighs)

24:34.048 --> 24:36.215
(intro to "God Knows" plays)

24:36.383 --> 24:41.061
DOTTIE:
♪<i> Our love was built on lies</i> ♪

24:42.373 --> 24:47.467
♪<i> The truth is</i>
<i> I closed my eyes</i> ♪

24:47.487 --> 24:51.046
♪<i> And I see the red taillights</i> ♪

24:51.139 --> 24:54.325
♪<i> Of our life fade away</i> ♪

24:59.815 --> 25:04.076
♪<i> She's where you want to be</i> ♪

25:05.396 --> 25:10.749
♪<i> But we both know</i>
<i> you'll never leave me</i> ♪

25:10.901 --> 25:14.678
♪<i> So I'm left here bleeding</i> ♪

25:14.830 --> 25:18.140
♪<i> On these pages...</i> ♪

25:21.020 --> 25:24.170
She left this for him.

25:24.190 --> 25:25.748
The pain in her voice.

25:25.766 --> 25:27.674
Nicky,
I think he cheated on her.

25:27.693 --> 25:30.085
Daddy wouldn't cheat.

25:30.178 --> 25:32.846
It's about heartbreak
and cheating, yes,

25:32.865 --> 25:34.514
but so is every country song.

25:34.608 --> 25:37.017
-If that's true,
then why not record it?
-I don't know.

25:37.111 --> 25:39.428
Maybe she wasn't done with it.

25:39.446 --> 25:42.522
Or she just didn't want anybody
else to hear it but him.

25:42.616 --> 25:44.600
-You've been cheated on before.
-All right.

25:44.693 --> 25:46.359
But Daddy is not...
he's not Clive.

25:46.379 --> 25:48.379
Well, he ain't a saint, either.

25:53.778 --> 25:55.535
(sighs)
Well, if that's true,

25:55.555 --> 25:58.556
then all this time,
I've been living up to their...

25:58.783 --> 26:02.117
shining, perfect example, and...

26:02.210 --> 26:05.804
Is anyone's marriage
what it's supposed to be?

26:05.956 --> 26:06.981
Mine is.

26:08.050 --> 26:09.641
Well, with Mama gone,
there's only

26:09.794 --> 26:11.627
one way to find out the truth.

26:11.720 --> 26:13.796
-Talk to Daddy.
-Mm-hmm.

26:13.814 --> 26:15.647
It's not fair.
You get to take your anger out

26:15.800 --> 26:17.132
on a pair of boots. I get...

26:17.225 --> 26:19.468
I get to take mine out
on a country legend.

26:19.561 --> 26:21.537
Great.

26:25.734 --> 26:28.127
(knocking)

26:30.831 --> 26:32.981
-Mom?
-Yeah?

26:33.000 --> 26:36.093
Something just came in
under the door.

26:38.005 --> 26:40.097
Maybe it's
your Monarch contract.

26:40.991 --> 26:42.600
Oh, my God!

26:43.677 --> 26:47.438
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
Oh, my God! (laughs)

26:47.665 --> 26:49.064
Is it?

26:53.354 --> 26:54.837
No.

26:54.930 --> 26:56.839
No, it's nothing
for you to worry about.

26:56.932 --> 26:59.524
-Hmm.
-Well, I have good news.

26:59.677 --> 27:00.784
Yeah?

27:00.936 --> 27:04.163
Ace Roman follows me
on Instagram.

27:05.366 --> 27:07.625
<i> Mija.</i>

27:08.628 --> 27:10.202
Less social media, more guitar.

27:10.354 --> 27:13.255
Eyes on the prize, baby.

27:16.710 --> 27:20.045
My marriage is none
of your business, Nicolette.

27:20.197 --> 27:22.330
Of course it is.
You and Mama set an example

27:22.383 --> 27:24.958
that I've spent half of my
adult life trying to live up to,

27:25.127 --> 27:27.311
so if it's all a lie,
I'd like to know.

27:29.798 --> 27:32.207
I loved your mother.

27:32.300 --> 27:35.152
Unconditionally,
with all my heart.

27:35.379 --> 27:36.612
But?

27:39.066 --> 27:41.049
It was 40 years ago.

27:42.052 --> 27:45.496
It was one night
and a lifetime of regret.

27:47.667 --> 27:49.074
Did Mama know?

27:49.226 --> 27:50.893
The whole damn time.

27:50.953 --> 27:53.912
She told me
right before she died.

27:54.915 --> 27:56.915
I guess she found a way
to forgive me

27:57.067 --> 27:59.751
whether I deserved it or not.

27:59.828 --> 28:01.920
She made a choice,

28:02.072 --> 28:04.223
and it kept our family together.

28:06.352 --> 28:08.352
What choice would she want me
to make?

28:08.503 --> 28:11.605
Did that pasty limey
cheat on you again?

28:16.603 --> 28:18.845
You asked
what Mama would want you to do.

28:18.864 --> 28:21.014
Well, Mama's gone,

28:21.033 --> 28:23.701
so do what you need to do
for you.

28:24.778 --> 28:26.995
<i> (jet engine whirring)</i>

28:28.690 --> 28:31.375
♪ ♪

28:36.865 --> 28:38.549
Clive! Hi, bunny.

28:38.700 --> 28:40.509
NICKY:
Hello, Imogen.

28:41.795 --> 28:43.462
Come on in.

28:43.614 --> 28:45.222
I won't bite.

28:58.963 --> 29:01.071
♪ ♪

29:08.438 --> 29:12.458
♪<i> It's just a matter of time</i> ♪

29:12.643 --> 29:16.661
♪<i> Before I have to</i>
<i> pay the price</i> ♪

29:16.814 --> 29:20.758
♪<i> For what I done</i> ♪

29:20.834 --> 29:23.010
♪<i> Back there</i> ♪

29:25.172 --> 29:28.414
♪<i> I am bound</i> ♪

29:28.434 --> 29:31.602
♪<i> For my fate</i> ♪

29:33.196 --> 29:36.607
♪<i> I got bad man's blood</i> ♪

29:36.758 --> 29:39.425
♪<i> In my veins.</i> ♪

29:39.445 --> 29:41.987
-(grunts angrily)
-(glass shatters)

29:44.283 --> 29:46.784
♪ ♪

29:47.011 --> 29:49.602
(clamoring)

29:49.622 --> 29:52.456
-(camera shutters clicking)
-(clamoring continues)

29:52.625 --> 29:55.108
-Hey. Thank you.
-Wade!

29:55.127 --> 29:56.293
-So who's going to win tonight?
-Hey,

29:56.444 --> 29:58.295
my money is always
on Nicky Roman.

29:58.522 --> 30:00.631
♪<i> Ooh!</i> ♪

30:00.858 --> 30:03.717
(crowd chatter)

30:05.453 --> 30:08.454
♪<i> Hmm, you've been</i>
<i> wearing that crown</i> ♪

30:08.532 --> 30:10.365
♪<i> And tearing me down,</i>
<i> it's been a while</i> ♪

30:10.384 --> 30:13.143
♪<i> Since you've treated me right,</i>
<i> you've strung me along</i> ♪

30:13.295 --> 30:16.814
♪<i> For far too long 'cause</i>
<i> I never gave up the fight</i> ♪

30:16.965 --> 30:21.467
♪<i> Oh, my, oh, my, huh</i> ♪

30:21.636 --> 30:24.396
♪<i> Mama always told me</i>
<i> that I should play nice</i> ♪

30:24.565 --> 30:27.065
♪<i> But she didn't know you</i>
<i> when she gave me that advice</i> ♪

30:27.159 --> 30:28.992
♪<i> I'm through with you</i> ♪

30:29.144 --> 30:31.477
♪<i> You're one bridge</i>
<i> I'd like to burn</i> ♪

30:31.497 --> 30:33.221
-♪<i> Bottle up the ashes...</i> ♪
-For you.

30:33.315 --> 30:35.407
Nicky, why are you in black?

30:35.501 --> 30:39.077
Because this is the funeral
of my marriage.

30:39.171 --> 30:40.912
This is my friend, Imogen Lowe.

30:41.006 --> 30:43.231
Why is Imogen here?

30:43.325 --> 30:44.490
Because it's always
the other woman

30:44.510 --> 30:47.085
that's painted as a slut
or a home-wrecker

30:47.179 --> 30:49.329
or the wife that deserves
to be cheated on

30:49.348 --> 30:50.922
because she's cold or unloving.

30:51.091 --> 30:53.333
So, instead of blaming
one another...

30:53.410 --> 30:55.352
We're joining together
in solidarity

30:55.579 --> 30:58.171
to hold accountable
the only truly guilty party,

30:58.190 --> 31:01.507
which is my lying,
cheating husband.

31:01.527 --> 31:04.344
(applause and cheering)

31:05.606 --> 31:11.093
♪<i> Delta Dawn, what's</i>
<i> that flower you have on?</i> ♪

31:11.186 --> 31:17.690
♪<i> Could it be a faded rose</i>
<i> from days gone by?</i> ♪

31:17.710 --> 31:20.377
♪<i> And did I hear you say</i> ♪

31:20.604 --> 31:23.655
♪<i> He was meeting you</i>
<i> here today</i> ♪

31:23.716 --> 31:29.611
♪<i> To take you to his mansion</i>
<i> in the sky?</i> ♪

31:29.704 --> 31:32.130
GIGI:
That was a real baller move
out there with Imogen.

31:32.224 --> 31:34.683
-Thanks, Geeg.
-(phone ringing)

31:35.786 --> 31:37.636
-Hold on.
-Mm-hmm.

31:37.788 --> 31:39.563
Hello?

31:39.714 --> 31:41.231
He's where?

31:41.458 --> 31:42.566
Okay.

31:42.735 --> 31:45.310
-I'll go get him.
-What?

31:45.462 --> 31:47.220
Daddy's on a bender
down at the Shake and Take.

31:47.314 --> 31:49.389
I got to go pick him up
before the cops do.

31:49.408 --> 31:51.967
Daddy will be fine. What are...?
You need to perform.

31:51.969 --> 31:53.635
Why? So that you can prove

31:53.728 --> 31:55.746
that you're worthy
of that tour by beating me?

31:55.897 --> 31:57.748
No.

31:57.899 --> 31:59.808
♪<i> Then a man of low degree...</i> ♪

31:59.901 --> 32:01.660
Yes. (laughs)

32:01.754 --> 32:03.921
I know I'm new to this business,
but you don't have to

32:04.072 --> 32:06.815
outsing me or Tanya
to get what you want.

32:06.833 --> 32:08.500
You just need to be yourself.

32:08.594 --> 32:12.320
And what if I told you that I
don't know who that is anymore?

32:12.339 --> 32:14.598
Maybe that's not
such a bad thing.

32:14.749 --> 32:16.491
What are you talking about?

32:16.510 --> 32:19.436
Well, just this last day,
you surprised Clive

32:19.663 --> 32:21.496
and you surprised Imogen.

32:21.589 --> 32:23.848
Maybe it's time
you surprised yourself.

32:24.001 --> 32:29.112
♪<i> And did I hear you say</i>
<i>he was meeting you here today</i> ♪

32:29.264 --> 32:32.507
♪<i> To take you to his mansion</i> ♪

32:32.600 --> 32:38.121
♪<i> In the sky?</i> ♪

32:38.348 --> 32:40.499
(applause and cheering)

32:41.868 --> 32:44.294
Here.
Maybe this'll sober you up.

32:45.631 --> 32:48.614
Get on back to the show,
Georgina. I'm fine.

32:48.634 --> 32:50.208
What I have to say can't wait.

32:50.302 --> 32:52.711
-(truck door opens)
-Mama left something for you

32:52.863 --> 32:54.546
in the heel of one of her boots,

32:54.698 --> 32:57.432
like you were supposed
to find it there.

32:58.978 --> 33:01.553
When we'd be on the road,

33:01.705 --> 33:04.297
some of the band hid drugs
in their boots.

33:05.375 --> 33:07.967
Me and Dottie would hide
secret messages to each other

33:07.987 --> 33:10.153
where nobody'd find them.

33:11.048 --> 33:12.972
Well, I found it,

33:13.050 --> 33:14.658
and here's her message.

33:14.809 --> 33:18.078
(guitar plays slow, gentle intro
to "God Knows")

33:28.398 --> 33:33.993
♪<i> Our love was built on lies</i> ♪

33:34.087 --> 33:39.924
♪<i> The truth is</i>
<i> I closed my eyes</i> ♪

33:40.077 --> 33:42.668
♪<i> And I see the red taillights</i> ♪

33:42.879 --> 33:46.982
♪<i> Of our life fade away</i> ♪

33:50.678 --> 33:56.258
♪<i> You</i> ♪

33:56.351 --> 34:01.112
♪<i> You broke my heart,</i>
<i> my body and mind</i> ♪

34:01.206 --> 34:06.710
♪<i> The truth can't be spoken</i> ♪

34:08.213 --> 34:14.259
♪<i> But God knows I am broken.</i> ♪

34:16.388 --> 34:19.447
(song ends)

34:19.466 --> 34:21.391
(crowd chatter)

34:22.394 --> 34:24.394
(sighs)

34:24.546 --> 34:26.805
I'm looking forward to seeing
what Nicky does tonight.

34:26.899 --> 34:29.140
Well, prepare to be dazzled.

34:29.234 --> 34:31.142
I don't need to be dazzled.

34:31.236 --> 34:33.219
I need to believe that millions

34:33.313 --> 34:35.146
-of ticket-buying fans
will be dazzled.
-(applause)

34:35.315 --> 34:38.149
ANNOUNCER:
And now the next
Queen of Country, Nicky Roman.

34:38.318 --> 34:40.302
-(applause and cheering)
-NICKY: This is for all you

34:40.395 --> 34:42.245
out there who've had your hearts

34:42.397 --> 34:45.807
-ripped apart...
-(drumbeat mimics heart beating)

34:45.826 --> 34:47.417
...and then rose from the ashes.

34:47.494 --> 34:49.235
-(explosive popping)
-(applause and cheering)

34:49.329 --> 34:51.571
Who wants
to burn something down?

34:51.590 --> 34:54.257
-(applause and cheering)
-(explosive pop)

34:54.334 --> 34:57.594
(band plays lively intro
to "Kerosene")

35:00.933 --> 35:03.082
(applause and cheering swell)

35:03.102 --> 35:05.176
♪<i> Forget your high society</i> ♪

35:05.329 --> 35:07.771
♪<i> I'm soakin' it in kerosene</i> ♪

35:07.998 --> 35:10.107
(rhythmic clapping)

35:10.258 --> 35:12.592
♪<i> Light 'em up</i>
<i> and watch 'em burn</i> ♪

35:12.611 --> 35:15.503
♪<i> Teach 'em what</i>
<i> they need to learn, ha!</i> ♪

35:15.597 --> 35:17.930
(yelling, cheering)

35:17.950 --> 35:20.283
♪<i> And dirty hands ain't made</i>
<i> for shakin'</i> ♪

35:20.435 --> 35:24.362
♪<i> Ain't a rule</i>
<i> that ain't worth breakin'</i> ♪

35:25.532 --> 35:29.701
♪<i> I'm givin' up on love</i>
<i> 'cause love's given up on me</i> ♪

35:29.853 --> 35:32.045
(cheering)

35:33.281 --> 35:35.132
♪<i> Now I don't hate</i>
<i> the one who left</i> ♪

35:35.283 --> 35:38.468
♪<i> You can't hate someone</i>
<i> who's dead</i> ♪

35:40.697 --> 35:42.305
♪<i> He's out there</i>
<i> holdin' on to someone</i> ♪

35:42.532 --> 35:45.308
♪<i> I'm holding up</i>
<i> my smokin' gun</i> ♪

35:49.039 --> 35:50.796
♪<i> I'll find somewhere</i>
<i> to lay my blame</i> ♪

35:50.816 --> 35:53.859
♪<i> The day she changes</i>
<i> her last name</i> ♪

35:55.545 --> 36:01.366
♪<i> Well, I'm givin' up on love</i>
<i> 'cause love's given up on me</i> ♪

36:02.235 --> 36:05.704
♪<i> Oh, yeah, whoo!</i> ♪

36:07.908 --> 36:10.625
-(song ends)
-(applause and cheering)

36:17.067 --> 36:20.343
(laughing):
It's not true.

36:20.495 --> 36:22.086
Ah.

36:22.163 --> 36:23.922
<i> Ay, Dios mío.</i>

36:24.074 --> 36:26.308
-Mom.
-Mm?

36:30.022 --> 36:32.355
They're from Ace Roman.

36:33.250 --> 36:35.525
Stay focused,<i> mija.</i>

36:38.939 --> 36:40.605
What's that?

36:40.699 --> 36:44.108
It's a contract from Monarch.

36:44.261 --> 36:46.852
-Oh, my God. Oh, my God.
-(laughs softly)

36:46.905 --> 36:49.873
-(squeals) Oh, my God.
-(laughing)

36:50.100 --> 36:52.784
(both laughing)

36:52.936 --> 36:54.953
♪ ♪

36:55.047 --> 36:57.214
(Albie sighs)

36:57.441 --> 37:00.458
I'll always be sorry
for how much hurt I caused her.

37:00.610 --> 37:04.629
More so now that I know
how deep that pain went.

37:04.781 --> 37:07.641
It wasn't just her
you lied to and hurt, Daddy.

37:09.711 --> 37:11.228
I'm sorry.

37:11.455 --> 37:15.565
I carried this secret around
for a long time.

37:17.461 --> 37:20.403
I want to be better.
I just don't know how I can

37:20.630 --> 37:24.032
until I can make peace
with what I did to your mama.

37:26.820 --> 37:28.745
We can pay tribute to her here.

37:28.896 --> 37:31.414
The world might not see it,
but...

37:31.566 --> 37:33.541
she will.

37:34.736 --> 37:36.461
Good.

37:41.426 --> 37:44.552
(playing, soft, gentle intro
to "Always on My Mind")

37:49.101 --> 37:53.270
♪<i> Maybe I didn't love you</i> ♪

37:55.499 --> 37:58.566
♪<i> Quite as often</i>
<i> as I could have</i> ♪

38:01.505 --> 38:05.448
♪<i> Maybe I didn't treat you</i> ♪

38:07.602 --> 38:11.079
♪<i> Quite as good</i>
<i> as I should have</i> ♪

38:14.017 --> 38:18.128
♪<i> If I made you feel</i>
<i> second best</i> ♪

38:20.040 --> 38:24.968
♪<i> Girl, I'm sorry I was blind</i> ♪

38:26.287 --> 38:31.474
BOTH:
♪<i> You were always on my mind</i> ♪

38:32.811 --> 38:37.147
♪<i> You were always on my mind</i> ♪

38:38.633 --> 38:44.228
GIGI:
♪<i> And maybe I didn't hold you</i> ♪

38:44.381 --> 38:47.549
♪<i> All those lonely</i> ♪

38:47.567 --> 38:49.993
♪<i> Lonely times</i> ♪

38:51.330 --> 38:56.482
♪<i> I guess I never told you</i> ♪

38:56.501 --> 39:00.728
♪<i> I'm so happy</i>
<i> that you're mine...</i> ♪

39:00.747 --> 39:03.322
-Hey.
-Well?

39:03.416 --> 39:05.842
Full disclosure?

39:06.069 --> 39:08.920
Your connection
with the fans was electric.

39:09.072 --> 39:11.348
You were all heart
out there tonight, Nicky.

39:11.499 --> 39:13.016
And that's a good thing,
very good.

39:13.167 --> 39:14.667
Great. So I get my tour?

39:14.686 --> 39:16.186
We'll see.

39:16.413 --> 39:18.855
I work my ass off,
I blow the room away,

39:19.006 --> 39:21.599
I change up my act,
and all I get's a "We'll see"?

39:21.751 --> 39:24.176
I didn't say no.

39:24.196 --> 39:27.864
♪<i> I guess I never told you</i> ♪

39:29.016 --> 39:33.761
♪<i> I'm so happy</i>
<i> that you're mine...</i> ♪

39:33.780 --> 39:35.688
Hey.

39:35.707 --> 39:40.768
ALBIE and GIGI:
♪<i> Little things I should've</i>
<i> said and done</i> ♪

39:40.937 --> 39:44.122
♪<i> I just never took the time</i> ♪

39:44.216 --> 39:46.107
Thank you for the flowers.

39:46.126 --> 39:47.942
You're welcome.

39:48.035 --> 39:53.114
♪<i> You were always on my mind</i> ♪

39:53.133 --> 39:57.435
♪<i> You were always</i>
<i> on my mind</i> ♪

39:58.972 --> 40:01.789
♪<i> Tell me</i> ♪

40:01.883 --> 40:04.792
(phone buzzes)

40:04.811 --> 40:09.739
♪<i> Tell me that your sweet love</i>
<i> hasn't died</i> ♪

40:10.742 --> 40:15.912
♪<i> And give me</i> ♪

40:16.063 --> 40:17.580
(phone chimes)

40:17.732 --> 40:19.082
♪<i> Give me one more chance</i> ♪

40:19.233 --> 40:22.210
♪<i> To keep you satisfied</i> ♪

40:23.088 --> 40:25.296
♪<i> I'll keep you satisfied</i> ♪

40:28.242 --> 40:33.763
♪<i> You were always on my mind</i> ♪

40:33.915 --> 40:39.269
♪<i> You were always</i>
<i> on my mind</i> ♪

40:40.922 --> 40:46.443
♪<i> You were always on my mind</i> ♪

40:46.594 --> 40:52.356
♪<i> You were always</i>
<i> on my mind.</i> ♪

40:52.451 --> 40:55.285
(song ends)

40:59.458 --> 41:01.499
ALBIE:
Thanks for waiting for me,
darling.

41:03.295 --> 41:04.869
Heard you did your mama proud.

41:05.021 --> 41:06.278
Thank you.

41:06.298 --> 41:08.131
I feel good about it.

41:09.025 --> 41:10.717
Listen.

41:12.362 --> 41:15.621
What went on with that woman had
nothing to do with your mama.

41:15.715 --> 41:17.456
It was me.

41:17.476 --> 41:22.203
So, whatever you're feeling
because of Clive,

41:22.296 --> 41:25.732
he's the messed-up one,
baby, not you.

41:26.726 --> 41:27.967
Thank you.

41:28.135 --> 41:30.278
But as far as Dottie goes...

41:31.564 --> 41:33.064
I'm a bad man, baby.

41:33.216 --> 41:36.551
I mean, I'm the reason
your mama died.

41:36.553 --> 41:38.161
I broke her heart.

41:38.997 --> 41:40.663
No, you didn't.

41:40.890 --> 41:43.833
She was... beautiful and alive,

41:43.985 --> 41:48.079
and then she told me
what she knew, and...

41:48.231 --> 41:51.156
I'm-I'm the one
that deserved to die.

41:51.251 --> 41:53.158
No. That's not why she died.

41:53.253 --> 41:56.346
She died because she was sick.

41:56.573 --> 41:58.163
You are a good man.

41:58.366 --> 42:01.226
And you show that
every single day, even today.

42:03.021 --> 42:06.272
Hey. And I love you.

42:08.676 --> 42:10.693
Thank you, baby.

42:18.428 --> 42:20.537
-(brakes squeaking)
-(truck door opens)

42:26.545 --> 42:27.693
Daddy?

42:28.696 --> 42:31.047
Daddy, hurry. The police
might be on their way.

42:38.205 --> 42:39.872
It's not much further.

42:39.891 --> 42:42.100
Just right down here.

42:48.549 --> 42:50.066
Oh, hell.

42:50.217 --> 42:51.717
Somebody got here first.

